This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) because it focuses on the development of a computational tool for calculating binding affinity in drug development. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because the tool uses multi-stage pipelines of molecular simulations, which could involve machine learning techniques. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software) because the tool involves the management and analysis of large amounts of data. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because the paper discusses the evolutionarily selected genetic changes that can lead to resistance to cancer treatment.
